= Cylindrical Ortho =
#context: vop
#type: node

"""CVEX lens shader that produces a cylindrical orthographic projection for Mantra."""

== Overview ==

Cylindrical Ortho is a CVEX lens shader for Mantra that remaps camera rays into a cylindrical orthographic projection. The horizontal axis wraps around the full specified field of view, while the vertical axis spans a fixed world-space height rather than a perspective angle. This makes it suitable for rendering panoramic projections where the vertical parallax must remain constant.

Attach this node to the __Lens Shader__ parameter of a Mantra ROP or camera object.

@parameters

fov_h:
    #id: fov_h
    Horizontal field of view in degrees. A value of `360` produces a full cylindrical wrap-around.

height:
    #id: height
    Vertical extent of the projection in world-space units. Controls how tall the cylindrical image plane is.

@inputs

x:
    Normalized horizontal pixel coordinate from the camera.

y:
    Normalized vertical pixel coordinate from the camera.

Time:
    Current shutter time.

SID:
    Sample identifier.

P:
    Ray origin override.

I:
    Ray direction override.

@outputs

cvex:
    CVEX evaluation result passed back to Mantra.

P:
    Computed ray origin for the cylindrical projection.

I:
    Computed ray direction for the cylindrical projection.
